Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large-scale language models and knowledge distillation, which are topics that are often studied in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of generated examples, which could potentially fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. While the paper does not explicitly discuss computer vision or neural networks, these topics are often relevant to natural language understanding tasks and could potentially place the paper in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
